Sentencas: A high performance five-layered anode supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is developed by low-cost tape casting, co-sintering, and screen printing techniques.
Titulo: Development of high-performance anode supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The cell is composed of NiO/scandium stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) anode support, NiO/ScSZ anode functional layer (AFL), ScSZ electrolyte, lanthanum strontium ferrite (LSF)/ScSZ cathode functional layer, and LSF cathode current collecting layer.
Titulo: Development of high-performance anode supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of fabrication parameters on the cell performance are investigated and optimized, including co-sintering temperature, thickness of the anode support, and AFL.
Titulo: Development of high-performance anode supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of GDC ion conducting phase impregnated into both electrodes also are investigated.
Titulo: Development of high-performance anode supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The microstructure of the cell is observed using a scanning electron microscope, and the cell performances at various operation temperatures are evaluated by a fuel cell test station.
Titulo: Development of high-performance anode supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The high performance is attributed to optimized cell structure as well as increase in the oxide ion conductivity and three-phase boundaries of both anode and cathode layers by nano ion conductor infiltration.
